#### What's new in Red Hat Openshift
- Red Hat Openshift 4.19
  - Please join our OpenShift product managers for an in-depth OpenShift update live via [___YouTube___](https://www.youtube.com/live/_Hrhmj707ok) or[ _ _ _Twitch.tv___](https://www.twitch.tv/redhatopenshift/) on Monday, June 16, from 10 am to 11:30 am ET.

    - This is an exciting opportunity for you to interact directly with OpenShift experts and learn—alongside Red Hat—what's new in OpenShift! Have questions during the session? Please use the Q&A function in [___YouTube___](https://www.youtube.com/live/_Hrhmj707ok) or[ _ _ _Twitch.tv___](https://www.twitch.tv/redhatopenshift/) to get them answered in real time.

    - To learn about other OpenShift livestream events, subscribe today to the [___livestream calendar___](https://calendar.google.com/calendar/u/0/embed?src=redhatstreaming@gmail.com).

    - We hope to see you on June 16!

  -  **Can’t make the live session?** **  
Can’t make the live event? No problem! We’ll be posting the recording to our[ _ _ _OpenShift YouTube channel___](https://www.youtube.com/c/openshift), as well as to our [___“What’s New/Next in OpenShift” web page___](https://www.redhat.com/en/whats-new-red-hat-openshift), the latter of which will also have the slides.  
  
  -  **When?**  
Monday Jun 16, 2025 ⋅ 4pm – 5:30pm CET, 10 am to 11:30 am ET  
